Here's a scenario where I think `reset()` or `clear()` is useful:

A user is presented with a few choices: activate account, lookup account, reset password. Each of these actions will involve state saved in the session. But each action should be totally separate. So, if the user started on one action but found out that was the wrong one and switched one of the others, then the session state should be reset or cleared. We could do that as you suggest:

``` java
public ModelAndView startPoint(HttpSession session, HttpServletRequest request) {
  // Make sure the session is clean
  session.invalidate();
  HttpSession _session = request.getSession(true);

  // now use _session when we already had session
}
```

Or we could use an improved API:

``` java
public ModelAndView startPoint(Session session) {
  // Make sure the session is clean
  session.clear();

  // go about our business
}
```

